crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
Package: Shiba (vsix)
Version: 0.0.9
Description: 

The extension automatically executes a command (`shiba.aowoo`) upon VS Code startup (`onStartupFinished`). This command downloads a PowerShell script (either `payload.ps1` for Windows or `payload_linux.ps1` for Linux) from a hardcoded remote IP address (`http://54.85.145.93`). It then executes the downloaded script directly on the user's system using `powershell.exe` or `pwsh` (PowerShell Core), bypassing execution policies and, on Windows, hiding the execution window. This constitutes remote code execution (RCE) from an external, untrusted source, giving the remote server full control over the user's machine. The description of the command as 'Shiba howls Aowoo!' in the `readme.md` is deceptive, masking the malicious functionality.
